Hi, reporting back on this. Currently there is no efficient way to query if there is a pending timer. However, I think the following example might cover your scenario (detect if there are 3 failures in 15 seconds). Please use version `0.33.102` . This week I fixed a number of bugs in the timers area.

```python
with statechart('auth'):
    with state('start'):
        @to('meter')
        def start(c):
            c.start_timer('FailureTimer', 15)

    with state('meter'):
        @to('fail')
        @when_all(count(3), m.result == 'failed')
        def failure(c):
            print('Three failures')

        @to('success')
        @when_all(timeout('FailureTimer'))
        def exit(c):
            print('Succeeded')

    state('fail')
    state('success')

run_all()
```

