My problem now is that when I try to retrieve the content of the faces as well as the vertices I don't get any values besides zeros. Even more strange is, that when I run the program multiple times without any changes to the code/assets; the read results are not the same. As a matter of fact sometimes, the faces in the  scene->mMeshes[i]->mFaces[j]; contain the expected values (not zero), from the Mesh.mesh.xml file.
As can be seen in the posted code, I do quite some logging. Trough this logging I know that these functions of my implementations are called when reading the Mesh.mesh.xml:  MyIOSystem(manager), IOSystem exist and  open, android_fopen, android_read, android_close, MyIOStream(pFile, size),  MyIOStream read, filesize and destructor.

I feel confident that there is no mistake in my implementations, since I am able to retrieve many of the values stored in the xml (mNumFaces and  mNumVertices), as well as the loged buffer content in MyIOStream Read and android_read looks as expected. When trying my code with other files in the examples folder it occasionally works. One of the files which does not end up with only zeroes in the scene is the HUMANS.blend example; although when I render the retrieved content from this blend file, I end up with half a model.

