You have it almost correct. But the `config_hook` decorator has to go with the hook:

``` python
    ex = Experiment() 

    @ex.config_hook
    def hook(config, command_name, logger):
        config.update({'hook': True})
        return config
    
    @ex.automain
    def main(hook, other_config):
        do_stuff()
```
The config hooks are executed [during initialization](https://github.com/IDSIA/sacred/blob/master/sacred/initialize.py#L121). But you are certainly right, in that the documentation could clearly be improved.

